  "local_port": 35916,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What universities does CRA International recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Charles River Associates (CRA International) is a prominent global consulting firm that provides expertise in areas such as economics, finance, strategy, and litigation. When it comes to recruiting new graduates, CRA International focuses on sourcing talent from a diverse range of reputable universities and looks for candidates with strong analytical and problem-solving skills. Here's an overview of their recruitment approach:\n\n### **Universities CRA International Recruits From**\n\nWhile CRA International recruits from a broad spectrum of universities globally, they tend to focus on institutions known for their strong programs in relevant fields. Some of the universities frequently targeted by CRA include:\n\n- **United States:**\n  - **Ivy League Schools:** Harvard University, Princeton University, Yale University, Columbia University, University of Pennsylvania, Dartmouth College, Brown University, and Cornell University.\n  - **Major Research Universities:** Stanford University, Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), University of California\u2014Berkeley, University of Chicago, Northwestern University, New York University, and Duke University.\n  - **Liberty and Specialized Institutions:** University of Michigan, University of Virginia, University of Texas at Austin, and New York University.\n\n- **International:**\n  - **United Kingdom:** University of Cambridge, University of Oxford, London School of Economics (LSE), Imperial College London, and University College London (UCL).\n  - **Canada:** University of Toronto, McGill University, University of British Columbia, and University of Waterloo.\n  - **Europe and Other Regions:** Universities such as INSEAD (France/Singapore), ETH Zurich (Switzerland), National University of Singapore (NUS), and others with strong analytical and economic programs.\n\nIt's important to note that while CRA targets these prestigious institutions, they also consider candidates from a wide array of other universities, especially those that demonstrate strong academic performance, research capabilities, and relevant extracurricular involvement.\n\n### **Preferred Majors and Academic Backgrounds**\n\nCRA International values a diverse set of academic backgrounds that support their multidisciplinary approach to consulting. The majors and fields they typically seek include:\n\n- **Economics:** A strong foundation in economic theory and quantitative analysis is highly valued, given CRA\u2019s focus on economic consulting.\n  \n- **Finance and Accounting:** Understanding of financial markets, corporate finance, and accounting principles is crucial for many CRA projects.\n\n- **Mathematics and Statistics:** These skills are essential for quantitative analysis, modeling, and data interpretation.\n\n- **Engineering:** Particularly industrial and systems engineering, which emphasizes problem-solving and analytical skills.\n\n- **Computer Science and Information Technology:** Increasingly important for projects involving data analysis, computational modeling, and technological assessments.\n\n- **Business Administration:** Degrees focusing on business strategy, management, and operations provide practical insights applicable to consulting engagements.\n\n- **Law and Public Policy:** For roles related to litigation support, regulatory analysis, and policy advising.\n\n- **Physics and Other Sciences:** Strong analytical and research skills developed in these fields are transferable to many consulting tasks.\n\n### **Additional Qualities and Skills**\n\nBeyond academic credentials, CRA International looks for candidates who demonstrate:\n\n- **Analytical and Critical Thinking:** Ability to dissect complex problems and develop strategic solutions.\n\n- **Quantitative Skills:** Proficiency in handling data, statistical analysis, and financial modeling.\n\n- **Communication Skills:** Strong written and verbal communication abilities to articulate ideas clearly and effectively.\n\n- **Teamwork and Collaboration:** Experience working in teams, as consulting often involves collaborative projects.\n\n- **Adaptability and Learning Agility:** Ability to quickly learn new concepts and adapt to diverse client needs and industries.\n\n### **Application Tips**\n\n- **Networking:** Engage with CRA\u2019s recruiters through campus events, career fairs, and informational sessions to learn more about the firm and express your interest.\n\n- **Internships and Relevant Experience:** Gaining experience through internships, research projects, or relevant extracurricular activities can strengthen your application.\n\n- **Tailored Resume and Cover Letter:** Highlight your analytical skills, relevant coursework, projects, and any consulting or research experience.\n\n- **Case Interviews Preparation:** Be prepared to tackle case studies and problem-solving scenarios as part of the interview process, showcasing your ability to think strategically and analytically.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nCRA International seeks talented individuals from a variety of top-tier universities and diverse academic backgrounds, emphasizing strong analytical, quantitative, and problem-solving skills. If you\u2019re interested in pursuing a career with CRA, focus on building a solid academic foundation in relevant fields, gaining practical experience, and developing the soft skills necessary for effective consulting.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's recommended to visit CRA International\u2019s [careers page](https://www.crai.com/join-cra) or reach out directly to their recruitment team.",
